article.headline: Kent St. 61, Miami (Ohio) 45
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Omni Smith scored 17 points and Armon Gates added 13 points and seven rebounds to lead Kent State to a 61-45 win over Miami of Ohio on Wednesday night. Kent State (16-9, 9-3 Mid-American Conference) had a 28-16 lead at halftime and led by as many as 20 points in the second half. Isaac Knight hit two free throw attempts with 17:07 left in the only chances Kent State players got at the line. Tim Pollitz led Miami (12-12, 8-4) with 14 points on 7-of-12 shooting and five rebounds. No other RedHawks player scored in the double digits. Miami shot 57 percent (12-of-21) in the second half after shooting just 35 percent (7-of-20) in the first period. Kent State shot 46 percent (26-of-56) overall. The Golden Flashes outrebounded the RedHawks 31-24.
